remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKPathBuilder` allows you to assemble a path step by step by adding contours, lines, arcs, curves, and sub-paths. When finished, call `Snapshot()` to get an immutable `SKPath` or `Detach()` to transfer ownership. This type wraps a native Skia resource and implements `IDisposable`. Always dispose of it when done.

## Examples

```csharp
using var builder = new SKPathBuilder();
builder.MoveTo(10, 10);
builder.LineTo(100, 10);
builder.LineTo(100, 100);
builder.Close();
using var path = builder.Detach();
canvas.DrawPath(path, paint);
```
